{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_69","type":"agent_message","text":"The core issue is clear now: inside the native executable, `System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\")` is an empty string. That’s why the embedded Scala compiler can’t find `scala` regardless of metadata. I’m switching from metadata-only fixes to wiring the real test runtime classpath into the native test process, which is the only path that can make `dotty.tools.dotc.Driver` work here."}}
